cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.CL 

This paper deals with computer vision tasks such as semantic segmentation, object detection, and depth estimation, which are typically associated with the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. The paper also involves training a deep network using fully automatic supervision, which falls under the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. The use of motion segmentation techniques and adaptation to specific scenes in an unsupervised manner suggests relevance to the cs.RO (Robotics) sub-category. The paper also involves predicting relative depth from single images, which is a task that falls under the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with natural language processing tasks such as scene understanding, which is relevant to the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category.
